The Chronicle Chronicle Reporter ESTABLISHED in 2014, Agent House Freight Services has grown to be a one-stop clearing, transport and logistics company, which prides itself in effective and efficient clearing of cargo, freight forwarding and transport logistics services on behalf of clients globally. Its parent company Rome Moments (Pvt) Ltd offers superior quality transport service and has evolved from a traditional transporting company to an integrated modern service provider placing value on professionalism, credibility, quality, efficiency, flexibility, commitment and teamwork as well as customer focus, integrity, reliability and social responsibility. Agents House Freight Services aims at maintaining the lead locally, while working hard to overtake and lead regionally and globally in the provision of quality services. It has over the years managed to keep its focus on efficient service delivery and performance to exceed expectations of customers through quick, safe and economical world class solutions to suit their needs and that has given it the impetus to grow.  The company strives to be acknowledged as the leading firm in global supply chain management services, providing superior total quality logistics solutions to the benefit of its clients, guided by the principle: “Our Customer’s Needs are our focus as we generate solutions beyond Customer Expectations.” Among the key services that it provides are, customs clearing and forwarding, road freight — where it has its own trucks of varying capacities, air freight, rail and sea freight as well as warehousing Agents House Freight is licensed to act on behalf of its customers in the importation and   exportation, goods in transit, removal in bond, commercial customs clearance, documentation submission and processing by all modes of transport i.e. road, rail, air and sea, of goods and services. With its nationwide, continental and world-wide networking, all ports office links it is able to meet and satisfy all its clients’ needs. Its employees are a vital hub in the execution of its mandate as a custom clearing, freight and forwarding logistics company. <img class="size-full wp-image-628036" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/zimra.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/zimra.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/zimra-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Zimbabwe Revenue Authority (Zimra) Over the years, the company has managed to assemble a dynamic, loyal and innovative team of employees with intellectual energy anchored on diverse experience in supply chain management solutions. Its administration team comprises individuals with a minimum of 10 years’ experience each in freight and logistics across all facets of freight with in-depth knowledge of Zimra regulations and procedures. In response to globally expanding demand for timely clearance of cargo and freight forwarding logistics services, the agent has managed to establish other branches apart from its main office in Beitbridge and Harare with the approach and vision of spreading quality clearance at the country’s border posts that is Chirundu, Nyamapanda, Forbes and Plumtree.